President Obama spoke with Russian President Putin about the situation in Ukraine. Obama welcomed President Poroshenko's peace plan and urged Russia and separatist leaders to work with Ukraine to implement it. Obama asked Putin to press the separatists to recognize and abide by the ceasefire and to stop sending weapons into Ukraine. Obama emphasized that actions must accompany words and that the US is ready to impose more sanctions if needed. They also discussed removing chemical weapons in Syria and finding a peaceful solution for Iran's nuclear program.